cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper discusses transfer reinforcement learning methods, which involve leveraging experience from source tasks to speed up RL algorithms for a target task. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY), which often involve RL techniques. Additionally, the paper reports experimental results on a continuous chain problem, which could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if visual inputs were involved.
